rsDHCP.name: rsDHCP
rsDHCP.description: The private MIB module definition for DHCP server support in DLINK-3100 devices.

rsDhcpMibVersion.name: rsDhcpMibVersion
rsDhcpMibVersion.description: DHCP MIB's version, the current version is 4.

rlDhcpRelayEnable.name: rlDhcpRelayEnable
rlDhcpRelayEnable.description: Enable or disable the use of the DHCP relay.

rlDhcpRelayExists.name: rlDhcpRelayExists
rlDhcpRelayExists.description: This variable shows whether the device can function as a DHCP Relay Agent.

rlDhcpRelayNextServerTable.name: rlDhcpRelayNextServerTable
rlDhcpRelayNextServerTable.description: The DHCP Relay Next Servers configuration Table

rlDhcpRelayNextServerEntry.name: rlDhcpRelayNextServerEntry
rlDhcpRelayNextServerEntry.description: The row definition for this table. DHCP requests are relayed to the specified next server according to their threshold values.

rlDhcpRelayNextServerIpAddr.name: rlDhcpRelayNextServerIpAddr
rlDhcpRelayNextServerIpAddr.description: The IPAddress of the next configuration server. DHCP Server may act as a DHCP relay if this parameter is not equal to 0.0.0.0.

rlDhcpRelayNextServerSecThreshold.name: rlDhcpRelayNextServerSecThreshold
rlDhcpRelayNextServerSecThreshold.description: DHCP requests are relayed only if their SEC field is greater or equal to the threshold value in order to allow local DHCP Servers to answer first.

rlDhcpRelayNextServerRowStatus.name: rlDhcpRelayNextServerRowStatus
rlDhcpRelayNextServerRowStatus.description: This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'destroy' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceTable.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceTable
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceTable.description: The enabled DHCP Relay Interface Table

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceEntry.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceEntry
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceEntry.description: The row definition for this table. The user can add entry when DHCP relay is enabled on Interface.

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceIfindex.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceIfindex
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceIfindex.description: The Interface on which an user enables a DHCP relay

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceUseGiaddr.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceUseGiaddr
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceUseGiaddr.description: The flag is used to set a DHCP relay interface to use GiAddr in the standard way. Default is TRUE. The field is not supported.

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceRowStatus.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceRowStatus
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceRowStatus.description: Entry status. Can be destroy, active or createAndGo

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListTable.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListTable
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListTable.description: This table contains one entry. The entry contains port list and vlan lists of interfaces that have configured DHCP relay

rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListEntry.name: rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListEntry
rlDhcpRelayInterfaceListEntry.description: The entry contains port list and vlan lists of interfaces that have configured DHCP relay.

rlDhcpSrvEnable.name: rlDhcpSrvEnable
rlDhcpSrvEnable.description: Enable or Disable the use of the DHCP Server. For a router product the default value is TRUE. For a switch product the default is FALSE.

rlDhcpSrvExists.name: rlDhcpSrvExists
rlDhcpSrvExists.description: This variable shows whether the device can function as a DHCP Server.

rlDhcpSrvDbLocation.name: rlDhcpSrvDbLocation
rlDhcpSrvDbLocation.description: Describes where DHCP Server database is stored.

rlDhcpSrvMaxNumOfClients.name: rlDhcpSrvMaxNumOfClients
rlDhcpSrvMaxNumOfClients.description: This variable shows maximum number of clients that can be supported by DHCP Server dynamic allocation.

rlDhcpSrvDbNumOfActiveEntries.name: rlDhcpSrvDbNumOfActiveEntries
rlDhcpSrvDbNumOfActiveEntries.description: This variable shows number of active entries stored in database.

rlDhcpSrvDbErase.name: rlDhcpSrvDbErase
rlDhcpSrvDbErase.description: The value is always false. Setting this variable to true causes erasing all entries in DHCP database.

rlDhcpSrvProbeEnable.name: rlDhcpSrvProbeEnable
rlDhcpSrvProbeEnable.description: Enable or Disable the use of the DHCP probe before allocating an IP address.

rlDhcpSrvProbeTimeout.name: rlDhcpSrvProbeTimeout
rlDhcpSrvProbeTimeout.description: Indicates the peiod of time in milliseconds the DHCP probe will wait before issuing a new trial or deciding that no other device on the network has the IP address which DHCP considers allocating.

rlDhcpSrvProbeRetries.name: rlDhcpSrvProbeRetries
rlDhcpSrvProbeRetries.description: Indicates how many times DHCP will probe before deciding that no other device on the network has the IP address which DHCP considers allocating.

rlDhcpSrvDefaultNetworkPoolName.name: rlDhcpSrvDefaultNetworkPoolName
rlDhcpSrvDefaultNetworkPoolName.description: Contains a default network pool name. Used in case of one network pool only.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrTable.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrTable
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrTable.description: Table of IP Addresses allocated by DHCP Server by static and dynamic allocations.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrEntry.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrEntry
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrEntry.description: The row definition for this table. Parameters of DHCP allocated IP Addresses table.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpAddr.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpAddr
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpAddr.description: The IP address that was allocated by DHCP Server.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpNetMask.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpNetMask
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIpNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifier.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifier
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifier.description: Unique Identifier for client. Either physical address or DHCP Client Identifier.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifierType.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifierType
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrIdentifierType.description: Identifier Type. Either physical address or DHCP Client Identifier.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrClnHostName.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrClnHostName
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrClnHostName.description: Client Host Name. DHCP Server will use it to update DNS Server. Must be unique per client.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrMechanism.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrMechanism
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrMechanism.description: Mechanism of allocation IP Address by DHCP Server. The only value that can be set by user is manual.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrAgeTime.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrAgeTime
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrAgeTime.description: Age time of the IP Address.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrPoolName.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrPoolName
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrPoolName.description: Ip address pool name. A unique name for host pool static allocation, or network pool name in case of dynamic allocation.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrConfParamsName.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrConfParamsName
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrConfParamsName.description: This variable points (serves as key) to appropriate set of parameters in the DHCP Server configuration parameters table.

rlDhcpSrvIpAddrRowStatus.name: rlDhcpSrvIpAddrRowStatus
rlDhcpSrvIpAddrRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicTable.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicTable
rlDhcpSrvDynamicTable.description: The DHCP Dynamic Server's configuration Table

rlDhcpSrvDynamicEntry.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicEntry
rlDhcpSrvDynamicEntry.description: The row definition for this table. Parameters sent in as a DHCP Reply to DHCP Request with specified indices

rlDhcpSrvDynamicPoolName.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicPoolName
rlDhcpSrvDynamicPoolName.description: The name of DHCP dynamic addresses pool.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrFrom.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrFrom
rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrFrom.description: The first IP address allocated in this row.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrTo.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrTo
rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpAddrTo.description: The last IP address allocated in this row.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpNetMask.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpNetMask
rlDhcpSrvDynamicIpNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP addresses of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicLeaseTime.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicLeaseTime
rlDhcpSrvDynamicLeaseTime.description: Maximum lease-time in seconds granted to a requesting DHCP client. For automatic allocation use 0xFFFFFFFF. To exclude addresses from allocation mechanism, set this value to 0.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicProbeEnable.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicProbeEnable
rlDhcpSrvDynamicProbeEnable.description: Enable or Disable the use of the DHCP probe before allocating the address.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicTotalNumOfAddr.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicTotalNumOfAddr
rlDhcpSrvDynamicTotalNumOfAddr.description: Total number of addresses in space.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicFreeNumOfAddr.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicFreeNumOfAddr
rlDhcpSrvDynamicFreeNumOfAddr.description: Free number of addresses in space.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicConfParamsName.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicConfParamsName
rlDhcpSrvDynamicConfParamsName.description: This variable points (serves as key) to appropriate set of parameters in the DHCP Server configuration parameters table.

rlDhcpSrvDynamicRowStatus.name: rlDhcpSrvDynamicRowStatus
rlDhcpSrvDynamicRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsEntry.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsEntry
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsEntry.description: The row definition for this table. Each entry corresponds to one specific parameters set.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsName.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsName
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsName.description: This value is a unique index for the entry in the rlDhcpSrvConfParamsTable.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerIp.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerIp
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerIp.description: The IP of next server for client to use in configuration process.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerName.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerName
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNextServerName.description: The mame of next server for client to use in configuration process.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsBootfileName.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsBootfileName
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsBootfileName.description: Name of file for client to request from next server.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRoutersList.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRoutersList
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRoutersList.description: The value of option code 3, which defines default routers list. Each IP address is represented in dotted decimal notation format with ';' between them.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsTimeSrvList.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsTimeSrvList
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsTimeSrvList.description: The value of option code 4, which defines time servers list. Each IP address is represented in dotted decimal notation format with ';' between them.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDnsList.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDnsList
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDnsList.description: The value of option code 6, which defines the list of DNSs. Each IP address is represented in dotted decimal notation format with ';' between them.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDomainName.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDomainName
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsDomainName.description: The value option code 15, which defines the domain name..

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNameList.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNameList
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNameList.description: The value option code 44, which defines the list of NETBios Name Servers. Each IP address is represented in dotted decimal notation format with ';' between them.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNodeType.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNodeType
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNodeType.description: The value option code 46, which defines the NETBios node type. The option will be added only if rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNetbiosNameList is not empty.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsCommunity.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsCommunity
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsCommunity.description: The value of site-specific option 128, which defines Community. The option will be added only if rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNmsIp is set.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNmsIp.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNmsIp
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsNmsIp.description: The value of site-specific option 129, which defines IP of Network Manager.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsOptionsList.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsOptionsList
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsOptionsList.description: The sequence of option segments. Each option segment is represented by a triplet <code/length/value>. The code defines the code of each supported option. The length defines the length of each supported option. The value defines the value of the supported option. If there is a number of elements in the value field, they are divided by ','. Each element of type IP address in value field is represented in dotted decimal notation format.

rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRowStatus.name: rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRowStatus
rlDhcpSrvConfParamsRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.
